76561197970524443,Recommended,242550,31532991,Posted: 3 May,all,HooksGURU,"Rayman Legends is a constant reminder of what makes an outstanding platformer.From the very start of the game you are greated by a vibrant and cheery soundtrack, that sets the stage for the game's warm and engrossing experience. Ubisoft's artistic framework engine paints a canvas of equally vibrant, and often comically over-the-top design and mechanics. From the amazing time-synced musical level showcases, to riding on the back of a buggy-eyed mosquito, to swimming through the depths of an inflatable ocean; the scenes are simply amazing in each of their playstyles.Levels are introduced through a series of paintings. With each segment leading to the next, in a series of what feels like a never ending chasm of silliness and complexity. Mechanics are introduced to the player as each painting series is completed. Newer levels often offer a mixture of previously refined skills, and newer skills that may take time to master before moving on to later portions of each series. Rewards range from the game's currency (Lums), to trophys for mastering each painting, new characters, showcases of the previous Rayman Origins levels, to ""scratch tickets"" that offer random rewards placed in a gallery.Difficulty ranges from, ""oh, I jump over that mushroom,"" to, ""there is no way anyone can do that."" The replay value easily outweighs the expense in that regard.At it's roots, Rayman Legends is a platformer. However, it feels like there is so much more than a platformer going on at any given time. Influences from Sci-Fi movies, Rock & Roll hits, inside jokes of Tom Clancy's series, the greatly overused ""Zombie Apocalypse"" themes, and sprinkles of nostalgia to those who grew up with Rayman.There's just so much Rayman Legends does right.If you are someone that gew up with platformers like Mario and Sonic, or just someone looking to add some frustration to your life, and have a laugh about it...pick this game up. You won't regret it.Uplay required, controller recommended, 10 minute breaks a must!"
