,Recommended,242550,23443632,"Posted: 7 June, 2016",all,Evranu,"I love Rayman franchise. I admire the main hero since the first game, which was released back in 1995 and simply named 'Rayman'. The games were always very colorful and beautiful. I truly enjoyed 3D games like 'Rayman 2: The Great Escape' and 'Rayman 3: Hoodlum Havoc'. They took a lot of hours of my life and I remember helping my cousin to beat them. Every single time Rayman games amazed me with great soundtrack, great gameplay and gorgeous characters.'Rayman Legends' is no exception, it's very similar to 'Rayman Origins', but I dare to say that it's easier than Origins. Why? You can collect everything without much effort. Lums are quite easy to get in a first try, the same goes with Teensies. I still love this  game though. It's beautiful beyond measure. the art is truly breathtaking. The same goes with music, it's really catchy and I found myself humming to it quite often. Daily challenges are nice addition and they keep you busy, even after beating the main story.It's a pleasant game and I can't wait for the next Rayman's adventures. Hopefully, next time we'll see them in 3D, because till this day one of my favourite games is 'Rayman 2: The Great Escape'.To sum up, 'Rayman Legends' is truly enjoyable, not too hard but still a must have for platform games fans, and what is more important: for Rayman fans, just like me."
