,Recommended,242550,16740630,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,Yanahma,"As noted in my Rayman Origin's review, this game and its predecessor are two of the best platforming games to come out in recent years, far superior to Nintendo's Mario offerings.However this one, unlike Origin's, suffers a fault - one that is almost unforgivable. This was originally a Wii-U game, utilizing the touch-pad on the Wii-U for certain segments of the game. In this PC port, these segments still exist - rather than redesign the level to be more fun platforming sections, instead they ham-fistedly added a ""press Y to do a thing"" function that makes these sections occasionally fiddly and tedious.Other than that, this is more of the same (quite literally, as a good few dozen of Origin's levels make it into this one too as a bonus). Excellent music, theming and platforming. Highly recommend either of the recent Rayman games for any fans of platformers."
