,Recommended,242550,8564529,"Posted: 4 January, 2014",all,Hyperbolic Estrogen Chamber,"Like Origins, Rayman Legends is a super stylish platformer requiring a good amount of coordination and multitasking skill to play relatively well. Origins was already a very stylish game, and Legends gives even more polish to both the visuals and the soundtrack. The platforming itself is pretty tight, and a lot of the later levels don't allow much room for error.The game gives you a lot to do, including invaded (read: speedrun) versions of every level, daily and weekly challenges (for online bragging rights, mainly) and rankings on both lums and teensies collected. However, with a reasonable amount of skill I was able to 100% the game in about 20 hours."
,Recommended,242550,8531265,"Posted: 3 January, 2014",all,Der Zonk,"This game is definitly in my top games of the year list, and is probably the best 2D Platformer I ever played.The bad stuf first: You need UPlay, which is a stupid annoyance and this game is not so nice to play with a keyboard. I really recommend a controller.That out of the way: WOWEasy to pick up and play -  had a stressful day? Play one or two of the music levels and you'll feel releaxed and calm.Want a challenge? My controller has toothmarks from some of the time trial levels which get unlocked later on.But still the game is never unfair or discourages you so you just keep coming back until you get that sweet sensation of finally beating the level. And when you have you can go to the daily challenges and compete against other players.One thing I like to point out is the level design. Especially in the music levels but also in every other, theres a certain flow. You're almost playing yourself into meditation. Rayman Origins, I felt, had to much backtracking so that you get all the lums and unlocked more stuff. Here you have much less lums you have to collect to get a gold medal, so you can just play the game. Even finding the caged Teensies isn't pulling you out of the flow.On top: The visuals are just.... happy. Nothing against dark and gritty games, I love them, but this game is radiating with happiness and joy. In the animations, the background, the enemys. Everything just says: Have a good time - and you definitly will. Solo or with friends.If you have doubt: Play the demo, but I can't find a reason why not to like this game."
